-- Sunoco board ok's 10-pct increase in qtly dividend
-- 
-- Thu Feb 1, 2007 1:01pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/01/businesspro-sunoco-dividend-dc-idUSWEN341020070201

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Sunoco Inc. SUN.N said on Thursday 
its board of directors approved a 10-percent increase to the 
quarterly dividend. 


  The dividend of 27.5 cents per share -- up from 25 cents -- 
is payable on June 8, to shareholders of record on May 9, the 
Philadelphia-based oil company said.  Chairman and Chief Executive Officer John Drosdick said 
Sunoco's results, business outlook and strong financial 
condition "provide us with the ability and confidence to take 
this action."